      "description": "One-loop integral family $T_1$ for the NLO and NNLO QCD corrections to $q\\bar{q} \\to \\gamma^* \\gamma^*$. The family has 4 propagators $D_1,\\ldots,D_4$ (subset of the two-loop family $T_2$) forming a massless one-loop box with two adjacent off-shell external legs. Two momentum routings used. IBP reduction yields 3 master integrals: bubble ($T_1(1,0,1,0)$), triangle ($T_1(1,0,1,1)$), and box ($T_1(1,1,1,1)$). Bubble is trivial. Triangle result involves the single-valued Bloch-Wigner functions $P_2(z)$ and $Q_3(z)$, expressed through order $\\varepsilon^2$. Box result includes the basis functions $R_3^+(z,w), P_3(z), P_3(1-z)$, and $\\operatorname{Li}_3$ functions of $u/w, v/w, w/u, w/v$ ratios, given through order $\\varepsilon$. All results valid in Euclidean region ($s,t,p_3^2,p_4^2 < 0$); analytic continuation to physical region ($s,p_3^2,p_4^2 > 0, t < 0$) performed via $w \\to e^{i\\pi}\\bar{w}$ with $\\bar{w} = -t/s > 0$.",
